item.media:title: Red Devil Falls
item.media:description:
Support me on Patreon

Long exposure photo of Chute du Diable in Mont-Tremblant National Park, Quebec (Canada). Translated from French, Chute du Diable means Devil Falls (or Demon Falls). HDR composite from multiple exposures, and variant of Spectral Devil Falls selectively processed with red colors for a more surreal atmosphere.

Offered under a Creative Commons license / Attribution Unported. Meaning Yes for commercial use including premade backgrounds as long as you credit and link back to me. More details on my stock rules here: somadjinn.deviantart.com/journ…

For a small premium of 50 points you can download this stock at a high resolution of 5000 x 3333 px. Also available for purchase as a print.

Now included for download on my Patreon account if you want access to an ever-growing collection of my high res stock for one monthly subscription fee.

You can find this specific image at the following post: www.patreon.com/posts/red-devi…

Commission Info     Twitter     Tumblr     Pixiv     Youtube     Gumroad

 'Artistic freedom' commission work for ErebosReality - original character named Genevieve Alosis. Thank you very much for commissioning us!
Please don't use this work in any ways other than social sharing without ErebosReality permission :3

 I know she's actually not a thief, but this stare... why do I get the feeling that I already was pickpocketed? 
 Ahaha, Gig, you're a cat, you don't have pockets ^^
 In fact I have several 'natural' ones as an emergency  
 I... don't want to know anything about this aspect of your life  
 ...
 My thick fur, you spoiled girl! I was talking about the fur!

item.title: SMASH
item.media:title: SMASH
item.media:description:
I've followed the Super Smash Bros games since it's N64 days, it's amazing to see a culimation of the franchise come together in the release of Ultimate!

Having never done a painting that's taken me over 30 hours I wanted to tackle a large project for the first time. It was a really interesting experience to try a marathon rather than another sprint for this art piece, it ended up taking me roughly 200 hours!

Yes, DLC characters will be added as they're announced!

The 2nd Place Winner of July 2018's second Patreon Fanart Vote was Lucina from Fire Emblem !

Lucina's captors aren't exactly the most gentle and caring of hosts - probably something to do with her being responsible for most of their problems lately... but they can't let her freeze overnight either (kinda defeats the purpose of taking a prisoner, y'know?). Good thing she has that big ol' cape, huh?

Please also check out my Twitter and Pixiv accounts!

item.title: Lonely Night
item.media:title: Lonely Night
item.media:description:
Does anyone else feel as if you're art is not good enough for your own standards? But you cant effectively improve without actually drawing.
This is what happens to me most of the time I try to draw something but in the end i'm always happy because I've ended up with something that started from my imagination and ends up right in front of me, that's what I find so great about art.
And if you love that feeling, improvement will come naturally. So if you are struggling to improve, just remember creating an artwork that started as a blank canvas from your own mind is pretty amazing. 
Hopefully this will keep you guys motivated to keep drawing and to keep improving

I finally ended up drawing something after a long break so hopefully the ball keeps rolling and I will end up drawing more often again.  

Hope you guys like it!

item.title: Bright Green Holly Dragon
item.media:title: Bright Green Holly Dragon
item.media:description:
Hi all! I know it's been a while. I always suffer a bit of burnout around Christmas time which tends to cause me to disappear for a while, and this year was no exception. Between the holidays, moving, and getting sick, it's been an eventful month, but I'm feeling like working again, and so I'm finally getting back into the swing of things.

I know Christmas was over a month ago and this dragon is hardly relevant right now, but I really loved her design and wanted to share. I was working on a set of plant dragons over the summer, and thought it would be fun to make a Christmas-themed holly dragon. I love the contrast of the bright red berries against the various greens, and I worked in a bit of gold and red crystal as well. Really fun, I should give my dragons jewelry more often.

Crafted from polymer clay, glass bugle beads, and Swarovski crystal elements. Sold.

---

Want to see how my dragons are made? I sculpt live every Tuesday night from 7-10pm Pacific. You are, as always, invited to stop by and say hi over on Twitch. I'd love to see you there!

Plant dragons



------------------
HMD is on: Etsy | Facebook | Instagram | Twitch
Interested in commissioning me? I welcome custom work! Check my Commission Information for all the details
